  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pistachio-pesto-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle and peel your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint </strong>from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pistachio-pesto-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Set aside a few<strong> basil leaves </strong>and <strong>mint leaves</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>for garnish</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pistachio-pesto-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle </strong>and <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the tagliatelle is cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> tagliatelle & peas</strong>, reserve the pot and a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pistachio-pesto-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, add the <strong>peeled garlic</strong>,<strong> pistachios</strong>, <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>remaining basil</strong>, including the stalks, and<strong> remaining mint leaves </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half </strong>the <strong>lemon[s]</strong>, 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pistachio-pesto-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Blitz until you are left with a smooth paste – this is your<strong> pistachio pesto</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pistachio-pesto-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat and add the<strong> drained tagliatelle</strong> <strong>& peas</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pistachio pesto</strong> and stir gently until the pasta is coated in the pesto and everything is warmed through– this is your <strong>pistachio pesto tagliatelle</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/pistachio-pesto-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pistachio pesto tagliatelle</strong> with the <strong>reserved grated Italian hard cheese</strong> on top and a<strong> lemon wedge</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved mint</strong> and <strong>basil leaves</strong>, a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
